Subject: install.sh: allow repo URL override for local smoke tests

The Nadia migration cannot assume the public nadicodeai/argo release branch
already contains the unmerged migration. Local install smoke tests still need to
exercise the real installer and git install path, so allow the installer
repository URLs to be overridden by environment.

The defaults remain the official upstream URLs. Build-time rebranding turns
HERMES_REPO_URL_* into NADIA_REPO_URL_* in the shipped installer.

--- a/scripts/install.sh
+++ b/scripts/install.sh
@@ -40,8 +40,8 @@ NC='\033[0m' # No Color
 BOLD='\033[1m'
 
 # Configuration
-REPO_URL_SSH="git@github.com:NousResearch/hermes-agent.git"
-REPO_URL_HTTPS="https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent.git"
+REPO_URL_SSH="${HERMES_REPO_URL_SSH:-git@github.com:NousResearch/hermes-agent.git}"
+REPO_URL_HTTPS="${HERMES_REPO_URL_HTTPS:-https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent.git}"
 HERMES_HOME="${HERMES_HOME:-$HOME/.hermes}"
 # INSTALL_DIR is resolved AFTER arg parsing and OS detection so we can pick an
 # FHS-style layout for root installs.  Track whether the user gave us an
